310 g Chicken Breast Tenders
¼ cup Parmesan Cheese, shredded
227 g Broccoli
1 unit(s) Lemon
2 tbsp Mayonnaise
7 g Zesty Garlic Blend
2 unit(s) Russet Potato
4 tbsp Oil*
0.13 tsp Salt*
0.13 tsp Pepper*

Before starting, preheat the oven to 450˚F. Wash and dry all produce.
Remove any brown spots from potatoes, then cut into 1/2-inch wedges.
To a parchment-lined baking sheet, add potatoes, half the Zesty Garlic Blend and 1 tbsp oil. (NOTE: For 4 servings, use 2 baking sheets, with 1 tbsp oil per sheet.) Season with salt and pepper, then toss to coat.
Roast in the middle of the oven for 25-28 min, flipping halfway through, until tender and golden. (NOTE: For 4 servings, roast in the middle and bottom of the oven, rotating sheets halfway through.)

To another parchment-lined baking sheet, add broccoli. Drizzle 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) oil over top of the florets. Season with salt and pepper.
Roast in the top of the oven for 8-10 min, until tender.
When broccoli is tender, remove baking sheet from the oven.
Using the bottom of a measuring cup, press each broccoli floret until flat.
Drizzle another 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) oil over top, then sprinkle each floret with Parmesan.
Riast in the top of the oven for 3-5 minutes, until cheese is golden.

Meanwhile, pat chicken dry with paper towels. Season with salt and remaining Zesty Garlic Blend.
Heat a large non-stick pan over high.
When the pan is hot, add 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) oil, then chicken. Cook 4-5 min, stirring often, until golden and cooked through.**

Zest 1 tsp (2 tsp) lemon zest, then juice half the lemon (whole lemon for 4 servings). Cut any remaining lemon into wedges.
To a small bowl, add lemon juice, lemon zest and mayo. Seasoning with salt and pepper, then stir to combine.

Divide the chicken, potatoes and broccoli between plates.
Serve the lemon mayo on the side for dipping.
Squeeze a lemon wedge over top of the chicken if you like.